snippet.title: BALL PiT GAMES!! Daredevil Niko & Adley play in our new favorite indoor park (family night routine)
snippet.description:
learning flips so we go to the Trampoline Park!!

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Park Day Ever 1063

Do you guys know what one of my favorite parts of the day is? Coming home to Jenny and the kiddos after a long day at the spacestation! After a quick game of hide n seek, and doing new tricks on the bean bag, Jenny tells me that we are going to Urban Air, this indoor trampline park that we love to go to, especially when we can’t use the backyard!!

We jump in the purple Tesla and are off! We get there and right away the kids are super excited. We hit up the trampolines and the slides, the obistical course and the balance beam over the foam pit. Everyone is having a blast!!

Jenny remembers they have a whole different park here with rock walls and balance beams. We head over and it just looks like tons of fun!! We get in our harnesses and Aldey and I go first on the beams, Jenny and Adley have a race up the climbing wall and Niko is just the happiest little baby!!

After so much fun, it's time to head back home and go to bed. But not before we spend some time with our new pet Honey the guinea pig. Oh, and we have a surprise annoucment….. 

We love Urban Air, you should too :) -- 
https://www.urbanairtrampolinepark.com/locations/utah/clearfield
1659 East 1400 South
Clearfield, UT 84015

Learn how to make a Pikler Triangle! This was a really fun DIY project for kids that you can do yourself with some basic woodworking tools and some easy-to-find materials. We love rock climbing, so when a project came along where we could start to get our son interested, we jumped on it!

We'd love to hear your feedback!

The Pikler Triangle was developed by a Hungarian Pediatrician named Emmi Pikler many years ago and parents have been using it ever since to help kids improve gross motor skills, confidence, and teach them awesome skills. We love it, and if you're interested in building something for your kids, they're going to love this too.

If you make one of these Pikler Triangles please send us some pictures! We'd love to check it out!

TOOLS USED:
- Hand Drill - https://amzn.to/2Hgz4cG
- Impact Driver - https://amzn.to/2Fxtr7w
- Clamps - https://amzn.to/2Hq1GjS
- Chisels (Optional) - https://amzn.to/2En3WoS
- Tablesaw (Optional) - https://amzn.to/2TaegKQ
- Jigsaw - https://amzn.to/2CHEFWd
- Desktop Belt Sander (Optional) - https://amzn.to/2CEji8g
- Sandpaper - https://amzn.to/2CIFLkF
- Tape Measure - https://amzn.to/2C00Jv7
- Block Plane - https://amzn.to/2FwR5Rl

MATERIALS:
- Poplar (3/4")
- Birch Plywood (1/2")
- Birch Plywood (3/4")
- Climbing Holds - https://amzn.to/2HLiF0G
- Wood Glue - https://amzn.to/2Ts82pT
- Super Glue - https://amzn.to/2Tt0NOJ
- Blue Painters Tape - https://amzn.to/2tVFsOA
- Washers (8)
- Threaded Inserts (4)
- Machine Screws (2)
- Plastic Adjustable Knobs (2)

#Woodworking #Kids #DIY
